    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к иран. %i*ku-%i, вопросительной частице, обычно со значением
        ‘где’; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>kū</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_GIPh."/><biblScope>II 164</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="prc"><lang/><w>ku</w><gloss><q>где</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><biblScope>HFL I 263</biblScope></bibl>),
            <mentioned xml:lang="yai"
            ><lang/><w>kū</w><gloss><q>где</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="yai"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>куда</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"
                ><w>čikū</w><gloss><q>откуда</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>*kū(kw)</w><gloss><q>где</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>ku</w><gloss><q>где</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><w/><gloss><q>когда</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>если</q></gloss></mentioned>, (как связка придаточного
        предложения), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>ḱū</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>kū</w></mentioned> id. — По употреблению осетинский особенно
        близок к сакскому. Пространственное значение отчетливо выступает в дигорском %ikumæ%i
        ‘куда’, представляющем направительный падеж от %iku%i; ср. также <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_īsk0y"/> ‘где-либо’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nik0y"/> ‘нигде’. С
        течением времени в значении ‘где’ утвердилось <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kæm"/> |
        %ikæmi%i (др.иран. %ikahmi%i), а %ik˳y%i | %iku%i получило преобладающее употребление при
        временных и условных придаточных предложениях. — Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_k0yd"/> |
        %ikud%i ‘как’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
        57</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>18, 86,
                87</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                /><biblScope>45</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to Iranian %i*ku-%i, a question particle, usually with the
        meaning ‘where’; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>kū</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_GIPh."/><biblScope>II 164</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="prc"><lang/><w>ku</w><gloss><q>где</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><biblScope>HFL I 263</biblScope></bibl>),
            <mentioned xml:lang="yai"
            ><lang/><w>kū</w><gloss><q>where</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="yai"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>where to</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"
                ><w>čikū</w><gloss><q>from where</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*kū(kw)</w><gloss><q>where</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>ku</w><gloss><q>where</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><w/><gloss><q>when</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>if</q></gloss></mentioned>, (as a link for the a subordinate
        clause), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>ḱū</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>kū</w></mentioned> id. — The usage of the Ossetic word is the closest to
        сакскому. The spatial meaning is distinctly seen in Digor %ikumæ%i ‘where to’, which is an
        illative case from %iku%i; cf. also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_īsk0y"/> ‘somewhere’, <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_nik0y"/> ‘nowhere’. Eventually the meaning ‘where’ was taken by
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kæm"/> | %ikæmi%i (Old Iranian %ikahmi%i), and %ik˳y%i |
        %iku%i is used mostly with temporal and conditional clauses. — Cf. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_k0yd"/> | %ikud%i ‘how’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                /><biblScope>II 57</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>18, 86, 87</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>45</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
